From: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] pc-bios: ship apple-gfx-pci option ROM

The Apple ParavirtualizedGraphics PCI device loads an option
ROM from the host that the guest's UEFI firmware uses to
drive very-early boot (before
`AppleParavirtGPU.kext` loads in the kernel). On macOS hosts
the ROM is extracted at runtime from
ParavirtualizedGraphics.framework via
`PGCopyOptionROMURL()`; on Linux hosts we have no such API,
so the ROM must be shipped as a pc-bios blob.

Add `apple-gfx-pci.rom` to the `blobs` list in
`pc-bios/meson.build` so it is installed into `qemu_datadir`
alongside the other PC/pc-bios firmware blobs. The PCI core's
standard `romfile` mechanism (`PCIDeviceClass::romfile`,
loaded via `qemu_find_file(QEMU_FILE_TYPE_BIOS, ...)`) finds
it at device realize time.

**Note on the blob itself:** the current `apple-gfx-pci.rom`
blob in this series is extracted from Apple's
ParavirtualizedGraphics.framework as a development aid. It
is not redistributable under GPLv2. Before this patch is
acceptable for merge the blob must be replaced with an
in-tree EDK2 build that implements the minimal PCI option
ROM interface the guest firmware expects. That EDK2 port is
tracked separately; the blob is included here only so
reviewers can exercise the device end-to-end.

Signed-off-by: Matthew Jackson <matthew@pq.io>
---
 pc-bios/meson.build | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/pc-bios/meson.build
+++ b/pc-bios/meson.build
@@ -85,6 +85,9 @@ blobs = [
   'npcm7xx_bootrom.bin',
   'npcm8xx_bootrom.bin',
   'vof.bin',
   'vof-nvram.bin',
+  # Apple ParavirtualizedGraphics PCI option ROM (Linux port). See the
+  # note in the commit message about the current blob being a
+  # development placeholder pending an in-tree EDK2 build.
+  'apple-gfx-pci.rom',
 ]

 if get_option('install_blobs')
